  apps/sample/sensorFramework/plugins/iioPlugin/iioPlugin.c:599:66: error:
    %s directive output may be truncated writing 5 bytes into a region of size between 0 and 255 [-Werror=format-truncation=]
  599 |                 snprintf(resourcePath, sizeof(resourcePath), "%s/%s", resourcePath, "value");
      |                                                                  ^~                 ~~~~~~~
  apps/sample/sensorFramework/plugins/iioPlugin/iioPlugin.c:599:17: note:
    snprintf output between 7 and 262 bytes into a destination of size 256
  599 |                 snprintf(resourcePath, sizeof(resourcePath), "%s/%s", resourcePath, "value");

These warnings arise from using snprintf to modify the source buffer,
even though the standards clearly state that the result is undefined.

commits.commitMessage:
Initial development of the Sensor framework and plugins

- Plugins are components that provide read/write functions
  to the sensors.
- The sensor framework reads sensor data and populates it
  to datahub. The framework also provides a standard way to
  configure the sensors.
- Modify the mqtt sample app to publish all the entries in
  datahub periodically.

- Address code-review comments.
- Replaced local defines with equalivent defines from io.api.
- Added Makefile and CMakeLists.txt support.
- Added interfaceSearch section.
- Changed atof() calls to strtod().
- Removed dead code.

Resolves: LE-12146
Change-Id: I96c78041e494a9b82bdc068c3ae588a2fe686794
